{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "c7e8f9a0-aeps-chagans-0001",
    "name": "AEPS (Aadhaar Enabled Payment System) — Chagans Technologies",
    "description": "AEPS — Chagans.\n\n**Auth (fixes `AUTH_401` / Invalid authentication token):**\n1. Open **Variables** on this collection and fill **CHAGHANS_AEPS_CLIENT_ID**, **CHAGHANS_AEPS_CONSUMER_SECRET**, **CHAGHANS_AEPS_AUTH_TOKEN** (same values as `.env.local`), **or**\n2. Import `Chagans-AEPS.postman_environment.json`, paste the three values there, and **select that environment** in the top-right (not “No environment”).\n\nIf variables are empty, Postman sends blank headers → 401.\n\n**Bearer:** Put the **raw token only** in `CHAGHANS_AEPS_AUTH_TOKEN` (no `Bearer ` prefix); the collection adds `Bearer ` in the header. If your `.env` already stores `Bearer xxx`, either strip the prefix in Postman or you will send `Bearer Bearer xxx` and get 401.\n\nConfirm the token is **valid for AEPS** and **not expired**.\n\n**Headers map:** `client-id`, `client-secret`, `authorization: Bearer …`, `apiType: aeps`.\n\n**PAN & name (JIO KYC):** Use a real **individual** PAN (`merchantPan`). **`merchantName` must match the name on PAN / ITD records** exactly (order, spelling, initials vs full words). If you see *name is not matching with pan records*, fix `merchantName` and usually **`merchantDateOfBirth`** to match the PAN holder.\n\n**After merchant KYC (`kycStatus: validated`):** AEPS agent login is separate. If **3.1** returns `loginStatus: false`, `bankList: []`, `kycStatus: PENDING` — you still need a **successful 3.2 biometric login** on your route (e.g. **AIRTEL**). **Run 3.1 before 3.2/4.x** so `wadh` is saved into `aepsWadh` (used in PID / resident auth).\n\n**`Resident authentication failed`:** UIDAI did not accept the biometric — not a Postman JSON fix. You need a **certified fingerprint/face device + RD service**, **PID built with the same `sessionKey` / `wadh` / keys** as Chagans/Airtel specify, **good scan quality**, and **Aadhaar + mobile** matching the resident. Placeholder `pidData` in Postman will always fail. Use Chagans’ **mobile/SDK integration** or get **test steps** from them for your route.\n\n**Test data:** Variables include your HDFC `bankIin`, etc. **merchantId** default is your validated merchant. **txnId:** `{{$guid}}` on payments.\n\n---\n**Official API doc v1.0 (Jan 2026, Vineet Singh) — endpoint map:**\n| § | PDF | Postman |\n|---|-----|--------|\n| 2.1 | `POST /aeps/createMerchant` | **2.1 Create Merchant** |\n| 2.2 | `POST /aeps/merchantList` + query `page`,`limit`,`kycStatus`,`mobile`,`search` | **2.2 Merchant List** |\n| 3.1 | `POST /aeps/loginStatus` body `type`, `merchantId` | **3.1** |\n| 3.2 | `POST /aeps/aepsLogin` — biometric fields per PDF | **3.2** |\n| 4.1 | `POST /aeps/aepsPayment` — `type` withdraw/deposit/balance/miniStatement | **4.1** ×4 |\n\n**PDF vs live API (your integration):** The PDF does **not** mention **`txnId`** on `aepsPayment`, or **`wadh`** on login/payment — live calls required/returned them; this collection keeps them. PDF sample `merchantId` is not a valid MongoDB ObjectId. Real responses may add **KYC pipe** fields (`bankPipe`, `providerResponse`), **route** (AIRTEL/JIO), **`wadh`**, **`kycStatus`** on login status, and different wording (e.g. *Status check successful*). Ask Chagans for an updated PDF if you need contract parity.\n\n**Biometrics:** PDF §3.2 / §4.1 match — real **`pidData`** and device fields from certified capture; doc error *Biometric authentication failed* = same class of issue as resident auth.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
